Help a unique island and protect vulnerable marine life. Year round this specific island is surrounded by critically endangered hawksbill sea turtles, Tiger sharks (IUCN listed as near threatened) Thresher sharks (vulnerable) Scalloped hammerheads (critically endangered,) whale sharks & oceanic mantas (endangered) and more. 

Unlike most places  fishing here is extremely small scale (mostly only a small number of local fishermen from the island who use 1 hand line for fish for their families) so the largest scale threat to marine life at this particular island is marine debris from abandoned nets drifting in from other countries (which the dive boats and fishermen look out for) and surprisingly and unfortunately, from the local community the impact comes via marine debris because the majority use single use plastic water bottles DAILY. 

Please consider helping by sponsoring a water filtration system for a local family home in this very unique and significant-to-marine-life island. 
Help this small community transition to more sustainable eco-friendly alternatives and further show there is value in protecting marine life. 

The goal is to get a water filtration system sponsored for each of the roughly 1000 homes on the island so they can switch to glass bottles instead of single-use plastic water bottles which will help stop millions of plastic water bottles going into the surrounding water. 

A water filtration system is USD $325 and any donation made to this project through the international nonprofit @savetheseaturtlesinternational is 100% tax-deductible (for the US and some other countries.)

Smaller donations will help towards educational materials for the community and supplies like dive knives and reusable collection bags to help clean the near shore reef where sea turtles, fish, and sharks feed or frequent. 

