Those moments in life that take your breath away 💙💙 they were swimming in a train and then they turned and circled in around me tightly. It was one of the most special moments on my brief visit to dive with @oceanfanaticsmaldives @sideytheshark @reethibeachresort Bouncing from the shark project in Qatar to nearby Maldives. Manta rays are so intelligent, aware, and breathtakingly graceful. Spending time with the “birds of the sea” was both relaxing and thrilling at once, they are like sharks in their agility, but I was still extremely cautious not to kick or maneuver when they swarmed closely around me. If a manta swims up to you be careful or to kick him or her as sometimes they do pass very closely, they are harmless, and actually they need your protection from wasteful killing for the manta Gill-raker market Please learn more by researching:  #mantagillrakers and #MantaConservation

